'''Adi Granov''' is a [[Wikipedia:Bosnians|Bosnian]] artist who illustrated some of the ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]'' supplements for [[Wizards of the Coast]], as well as ''[[A Campaign Guide to the Centrality]]'', an article from [[Star Wars Gamer 5|''Star Wars Gamer'' 5]] written by [[Michael Kogge]].

An [[Wikipedia:Iron Man|''Iron Man'']] [[Star Wars comic books|comics]] and film veteran, he is providing covers for [[Marvel Comics]]' [[Star Wars: Darth Vader (2015)|''Darth Vader'']] [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] series.<ref name="Marvel.com">{{Marvel|url=news/comics/2014/7/27/22974/sdcc_2014_darth_vader|text=SDCC 2014: Darth Vader|nobackup=1}}</ref> He has also drawn the covers for the remastered editions of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']],<ref name="Newsarama">{{WebCite|url=https://www.newsarama.com/23013-marvel-remasters-original-star-wars-movie-adaptation-for-2015.html|text=Marvel Remasters Original STAR WARS Movie Adaptation For 2015|date=2014-12-16|archivedate=20190618121343}}</ref> [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']], and [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']]{{'s}}<ref name="Marvel.com2">{{Marvel|url=news/comics/24423/adi_granov_covers_two_classic_star_wars_adaptations|text=Adi Granov Covers Two Classic Star Wars Adaptations}}</ref> comic adaptations, as well as the [[Wikipedia:Emerald City Comicon|Emerald City Comicon]] variant cover for [[Princess Leia 1|''Princess Leia'' 1]],<ref name="FBGranov1">{{Facebook|username=Adi-Granov-Illustration|url=244587123597/photos/a.10152381013573598.1073741839.244587123597/10152896568293598/?type=1|name=Adi Granov Illustration|date=2015-03-04|archivefile=File:AdiGranov-Leia-March-4-2015.png}}</ref> and the [[Wikipedia:Forbidden Planet (bookstore)|Forbidden Planet]] variant cover for the [[Star Wars (2015) 1|first issue]] of Marvel's [[Star Wars (2015)|''Star Wars'' 2015]] series, which is based on one of his ''Iron Man'' pieces.<ref name="FBGranov2">{{Facebook|username=Adi-Granov-Illustration|url=244587123597/photos/a.10152381013573598.1073741839.244587123597/10152638902258598/?type=1|name=Adi Granov Illustration|date=2014-11-19|quote=I should also add, it was a client request to do Boba Fett in the Iron Man pose I came up with more than 10 years ago.|archivefile=File:AdiGranov-StarWars1-November-19-2014.png}}</ref>

Granov had drawn a Legacy variant for the [[Shattered Empire 1|first issue]] of Marvel's miniseries ''[[Star Wars: Shattered Empire]]'', but the cover was eventually canceled by [[Lucasfilm]].<ref name="BleedingCool">{{WebCite|url=https://www.bleedingcool.com/2015/08/17/lucasarts-pulls-adi-granovs-exclusive-cover-for-marvels-star-wars-shattered-empire|text=LucasFilm Pulls Adi Granov's Exclusive Cover For Marvel's Star Wars: Shattered Empire|date=2015-08-17|archivedate=20180619071939}}</ref>

